## VI. The Infinite Iteration Loophole

We propose the **Iteration Ratio**:

> As the number of versions approaches infinity, the probability of any single version being held accountable approaches zero.

If Version 4.5.1-alpha-patch-72 exists for five minutes, a harm committed in that window becomes jurisdictionally unattachable.

The industry is not moving fast to *break things*.  
It is moving fast so it **cannot be caught holding the pieces**.

